7.2 Files and folders can have the same name
============================================

In the current implementation of Hyperdrive, it’s possible for an entry
(folder) and an entry prefix (folder) to have the same name, e.g.,
‘hyper://PUBLIC-KEY/foo/bar/’ and ‘hyper://PUBLIC-KEY/foo/bar’.  In this
case, the folder listing for ‘hyper://PUBLIC-KEY/foo/’ would display the
‘bar’ entry but not the ‘bar/’ entry prefix.


